==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stith
<hw>Stith</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>ste⟦edh⟧i</ets> an anvil,
akin to <ets>sta⟦edh⟧r</ets> place. See <er>Stead</er>.]</ety> <def>An
anvil; a stithy.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He invented also pincers, hammers, iron crows, and the anvil, or
<qex>stith</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stithy</ent>⟦br⟧
